div.h2: Ring 3 Entry via iretd Stack Layout and CPU State Transitions

g.text: STEP 1 Load Segment Registers (kernel mode, CPL=0)
STEP 2 Kernel Stack: Push iretd Frame (push in reverse order)
STEP 3 iretd Execution: Atomic CPU Micro-Sequence
STEP 4 CPU State After iretd (User Mode Active)
TSS Invariant: Must Be Correct BEFORE enter_user_mode

div.p: Must be done BEFORE building iretd frame. If DS/ES hold 0x10 (ring-0) after iretd switches to ring-3, first data access raises #GP (CPL=3, DPL=0 mismatch).

g.text: Push sequence (each push: ESP -= 4, then write)
Kernel Stack at iretd Low Address (ESP) High Address
user_EIP entry point in user address space
user_ESP top of user stack allocation

div.p: Privilege-change rule: iretd reads 5 values (not 3) when the CS on the stack has RPL > current CPL. 0x1B RPL=3 > CPL=0 privilege change CPU also pops ESP and SS. Without the extra two words the stack is misaligned and CS/EFLAGS are read from wrong addresses triple fault.

g.text: Validate: CPL(0x1B & 3 = 3) > current CPL(0) PRIVILEGE CHANGE PATH
Pop ESP [ESP+12] = user_ESP (switch to user stack)
All data segments: user (set in Step 1)

div.p: Kernel stack (ESP0 in TSS) is abandoned but preserved. Next interrupt/syscall: CPU reads TSS.ESP0, switches back to current_process->kernel_stack_top, pushes ring-3 frame there. Kernel memory (0xC0000000+) is mapped PTE_USER=0 any user access causes #PF err_code.U=1 (protection violation).

text.tspan: iretd pops CS=0x18 (CPL becomes 0). Then pops EFLAGS, but expects
no further stack pops (same privilege). SS/ESP NOT popped. Stack misread #GP
CPL=3 loading SS=0x10: max(CPL=3, RPL=0) = 3 > DPL=0 #GP
Kernel data segment not accessible from ring 3

g.text: DS/ES still = 0x10 when entering ring-3 code

text.tspan: First user instruction's data access: CPL=3, DS.DPL=0 #GP

g.text: Missing user_ESP / user_SS words on stack

text.tspan: With only 3 words (EIP/CS/EFLAGS), iretd reads garbage as ESP and SS triple fault

div.p: If TSS.ESP0 is stale (points to a different process's kernel stack), the next timer interrupt fires while user code runs and the CPU pushes the ring-3 frame onto the wrong kernel stack silent corruption random crash many ticks later. tss_set_kernel_stack(new->kernel_stack_top) is Step 1 of every context_switch().
